{"commentv2": 1, "number": 9, "id": 1840921, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "UndercoverHobo", "body": "Hey, just thought I'd post as a thanks to Blizzard, though I should maybe do it on the forums... Oh well it's early, enough rambling.\r\n\r\nI'm a role-player on WoW and after reading this and it bringing light to thoughts I've had before, I thought I would share them.  A lot of people get upset that they don't get lore for their race with new patches, I've been upset with that at times too, but then I realized something.  We may not get the lore we always want, but look at how much time, effort, and thought Blizzard puts into making new lore interesting and exciting, even connecting it with little history from our world's past, and they do this all for us, they eve taught me a bit today after reading these posts.  Blizzard does so much to make this game a joyous experience in all aspects to all players, and I appreciate the work they have and continue to put in this game.\r\nThank you, Blizzard\r\n(As always, my apologies for the wall of text.)", "date": "2013-04-09T08:08:42-05:00", "rating": 12, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I assume you're referring to the whiny Night Elf fanboys on the forums? Those guys will never be happy with anything.", "creationdate": "2013-09-28T02:15:38-05:00", "id": 696999, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1840921, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "radicarl", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 10, "id": 1844048, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "lightclaw", "body": "[b]LFR Strategy[/b]:\nThis is the hard fight of this wing, but only because it has mechanics that need to be followed.  Once the raid gets the hang of the mechanics, the fight is fairly straightforward (if high damage and long.)\n\n[b]Entire Raid[/b]:\n This guy has a whole bunch of abilities, but with DBM and common sense they won't cause you much trouble.  However, there are four mechanics in this fight that are particularly important to note.  Once you get them down, you've got the fight done and it's just a matter of staying alive long enough to kill the boss. \n\n1. [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=136295]Overcharged[/url] - If someone near you gets Overcharged, they will grow to twice their normal size and get a lightning pool around their feet.  You have two options - A) Stack right on top of them and avoid the effect or B) Get as far away as possible (40 yards at least) and avoid the effect.  If you are closer, you'll take large amounts of damage and get stunned.\n\n2. [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=135695]Static Shock[/url] - The affected player gets a blue arrow over his or her head and an 8 yard circle around the feet.  After 8 seconds they explode doing a bunch of damage, shared by everyone in the circle.  Stack on people with blue arrows (and for goodness sake don't run away if you've got the arrow...)\n\n3. Bouncing Bolt ([url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=69013]Diffused Lightning[/url] adds) - The boss throws a bolt of lightning that bounces across the platform.  Its landing site is denoted by a small, blue swirly circle. Someone has to stand in the circle and get hit by the lightning bolt when it bounces through.  If this does not happen, an add spawns.  During the intermission, dozens of adds can spawn in just a few seconds if people don't follow this mechanic.  (Note: This is different from the large, whitish swirly circle from [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=135095]Thunderstruck[/url].)\n\n4. [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=135991]Diffusion Chain[/url] - A chain lightning type ability that causes an annoying add to spawn for every single person hit.  Spread out to avoid the effect.\n\n[u]Tanks[/u]:\nTank the boss near a pillar.  Each pillar provides the boss with a special power, and the level of the pillar can be seen by counting the rings of lightning it has.  When the pillar reaches three levels (three rings of lightning) it becomes supercharged and more dangerous (though not deadly in LFR.)  Move the boss from pillar to pillar to prevent any of them from charging completely.  After the intermissions, pieces of the platform become electrified and should be avoided.\n\n- We chose Bouncing Bolt to start with so that we could eliminate the adds after the first intermission, but your raid may prefer a different pillar.  \n\nDuring the first phase, swap after each [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=134916]Decapitate[/url], and the tank who is focused for Decapitate should run away (the ability does less damage the farther you move, but you really don't have to go far on LFR.)\n\nAfter the first phase the fight becomes a single tank fight.  There is an intended tank swap later but it is unnecessary in LFR.  It's much easier for the tanks to stick to boss or adds rather than trying to swap (there may or may not even be adds to deal with.)\n\nThroughout the fight the adds should be gathered up so that they can be AoE'ed down, preferably on top of the boss.\n\n[u]DPS[/u]:\nKill adds whenever possible.  When the boss casts Thunderstruck, get away from the large swirly mark on the ground.  Follow the mechanics for the four abilities that I noted above. (Stack on Overcharged or Static Shock, stand in small blue puddles to prevent adds, and spread out for diffusion chain.)  During intermission, spread out around the platform and continue following those mechanics.  \n\n[u]Healers[/u]:\nThere is a lot of tank damage, particularly when the boss is being moved between pillars.  Raid damage is also substantial, but it came in bursts that looked worse than they actually were.  During intermission, try to spread out around the platform so that each quarter has someone healing.  Be sure to follow the mechanics that I noted above (particularly during the intermission, when they will all happen in turn.)  There is a pushback phase near the end of the fight.  As long as you don't run against the pushback, you can cast while sliding backward.\n\n[b]tl;dr version[/b]:\nThere are four abilities that you have to pay attention to or the raid will wipe.\n1. Overcharged - Stack on the giant person who is affected and it won't hurt you.  If two people are overcharged near each other, pick one (you'll still get hit by the other, but won't die.)\n\n2. Static shock - Stack on the person with the blue arrow to share damage.\n\n3. Bouncing Bolt - Stand on the small, blue, swirly puddles to keep adds from spawning.\n\n4. Diffusion chain - Spread out to avoid chain lightning/adds.\n\n[u]Tanks[/u]:\nTank the boss near a pillar until the progress bar gets close to full then move it to a different corner.  Swap after Decapitate and run away if you were the Decapitate target.  Pick up adds.  After phase 1 it's pretty much a single tank fight in LFR, or boss tank/add tank anyway.  Avoid the electrified quarter of the platform after phase 1 and 2.\n\n[u]DPS[/u]:\nFollow the mechanics listed above.  Adds > Boss.  When Thunderstruck happens (large swirly lightning circle) get away.  During intermission spread out on the platform but continue following the mechanics.\n\n[u]Healers[/u]:\nLots of damage all around, with high tank damage when moving between corners.  Be sure to follow the mechanics listed above.  Spread out during intermission so that the entire raid is getting healed.\n\n[b]Macroable version[/b]:\n[code]\n/instance Overcharged-Stack on player. Static Shock-Stack on blue arrow.\n/instance Bouncing Bolt-Stand in blue puddles.  Diffusion chain-Spread out.\n/instance Tank by a pillar, don't let bar fill. Swap after Decapitate.  Intermission = Scatter.\n[/code]", "date": "2013-04-16T22:48:07-05:00", "rating": 167, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This is mostly good stuff. The advice to tanks about getting a pillar to 3 rings is a bad idea as it will buff that ability to level 3 and make the fight harder. Fylwind has posted a comment with the correct conduit strategy.", "creationdate": "2013-05-04T17:58:24-05:00", "id": 656256, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1844048, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Crunchy101", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "if you ever let a conduit get to 2, you should level it all the way to 3. When you enter an intermission, a conduit at 2.5 energy will go to 3.5. A conduit it 3 will stay to 3. (level goes to +1 capped at 3, charge stays). Except for bouncing bolt (as long as it's soaked well), all the effects can be nasty when leveled, even on LFR. Overcharge will produce overlapping stuns that do enough damage to kill people hit by 2 or 3, static shock is a fair amount of damage to split, and diffusion adds will HURT when people are inevitably stacked when its timer goes off.", "creationdate": "2013-07-28T02:35:20-05:00", "id": 680959, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1844048, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Karsteck", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "static shock and overcharge can't target tank-spec players. Many 10man groups have one or both tanks solo a quadrant. (if you get a double bolt, soak one, pick up the add, soak the bounce. Either shade towards a quad with a healer, or self-heal). Or pair a tank with someone that can immune static shock if they get one, so you never have to let a bolt land.", "creationdate": "2013-07-28T03:57:19-05:00", "id": 680966, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1844048, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Karsteck", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2013-06-18T00:36:58-05:00", 2, "lightclaw"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 11, "id": 1844577, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Patros", "body": "Conduit selection is really all about setting up the second intermission the way you want it, because the first intermission will always have all four active.\n\nThis boils down to two choices:  \n(1) Which conduit do you want disabled during the second intermission?  \n(2) Which conduit can you live with being leveled up during the second intermission?\n\nTo clarify the second question, unless your dps is extremely high, you're going to end up with one leveled-up conduit by the end of phase 2.  You'll have something like 90, 90, 130.\n\n\nMy guild was successful by (1) disabling diffusion chain so there is no reason to avoid stacking and (2) leveling up overcharge.  You can minimize the difficulty of multiple overcharge targets at the end of ph2 and in intermission2 by good stacking at the right times.", "date": "2013-04-18T09:19:38-05:00", "rating": -8, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "We found hero in phase2 let us avoid leveling anything, without calling our DPS \"extremely high\". On 10man, we've had good results with destroying diffusion first, but other groups have good results destroying static shock first. Seems less useful if you have tanks soloing 2 of the 3 quadrants for 2nd intermission, as static shock won't hurt anyone with 8 soakers.", "creationdate": "2013-07-28T04:03:57-05:00", "id": 680968, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1844577, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Karsteck", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2013-04-18T23:13:58-05:00", 1, "Patros"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 12, "id": 1844597, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "decembre", "body": "In LFR, it's possible to single tank Lei Shen through the first phase, and possibly through the second if DPS is heavy enough. [spell=134916] can easily be shrugged off and the debuff falls off before he casts it again. [spell=136478] will stack, but if DPS is fast enough, it may be possible to push him to the second intermission before it becomes too much to heal through.\r\n\r\nI found this out when our LFR's tank quit and I got frustrated with the DPS not knowing the mechanics. So with only four healers, we decided to pull to let DPS practice the fight and surprisingly almost got to the start of the second intermission.", "date": "2013-04-18T10:01:32-05:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 13, "id": 1845231, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "Molybdenum33", "body": "Has anyone defeated the whole raid on heroic yet?", "date": "2013-04-20T13:18:29-05:00", "rating": -12, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I think so, there are some comments about a guild defeating Ra-den roughly 10 days ago.", "creationdate": "2013-04-21T19:22:48-05:00", "id": 652810, "rating": -2, "commentid": 1845231, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Dragge", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Method world first 25 HC.", "creationdate": "2013-04-25T12:00:26-05:00", "id": 653708, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1845231, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "ceasure", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Dream Paragon WF10Man and WF (Even if 10 and 25 isn't compareable) March 24. Method WF25Man March 26. If we include Ra-den, Method was WF and WF25Man April 11 and Paragon WF10Man April 17. Most guilds define Lei Shen as the true endboss though, since Ra-den is way too easy in comparison.", "creationdate": "2013-05-01T16:07:51-05:00", "id": 655432, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1845231, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Nikeyeia", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 14, "id": 1849173, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Tarcalion", "body": "[url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=68397]Lei Shen[/url] is Mandarin Chinese, and the characters are  \u96f7\u795e (pinyin same as the normal English name), which means \"Thunder/Lightning God\".\n\nFor other fun ones, I'm guessing [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=62983]Lei Shi[/url] is Thunder Stone \u96f7\u77f3, [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=69712]Ji-kun[/url] is tricky, but I'm guessing they were going for \u9e21\u9da4, the 2nd character being a mythological large bird, like a roc, while the 1st character is chicken. [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=60999]Sha[/url] probably comes from \u6740, to kill. \n\nThere are lots of names I can't even remember right now with some fun meanings. The development team probably had a good time with that. \n\n[b][u]Note[/u][/b] -- the Romanization of some of the characters in game is [u]very[/u] inconsistent, fluctuating between Wade-Giles (Pe-king) and Pinyin (Bei-jing). Also, some Chinese-looking names aren't actual Chinese phonemes (Qon, Quilen), at least not Mandarin.", "date": "2013-05-02T05:07:17-05:00", "rating": 51, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I had assumed that the word Ji-Kun was just an eastern looking form of chicken.", "creationdate": "2013-05-07T07:50:27-05:00", "id": 656883, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1849173, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "ExcitedSoup", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Quilen is probably related to the Chinese mythological animal Qilin (\u9e92\u9e9f). Although I'm confused why Lei Shi would be Thunder Stone, she's a water spirit. I mean it's hard to guess based on just the romanization since it's missing the tones as well which PinYin would have had.", "creationdate": "2013-06-19T10:01:41-05:00", "id": 670387, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1849173, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "misosoup7", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2013-05-02T05:12:49-05:00", 1, "Tarcalion"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 15, "id": 1852569, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "zharshoul", "body": "Anyone notice how after the 2nd intermission when he says the bottom phrase he sounds like hes crying ,  as if hes thinking (OMG IM LOSING! NO THIS CANNOT BE)\n\n[i]NO! You are UNWORTHY! I ... AM.... THE THUNDER KING![/i]", "date": "2013-05-12T19:04:18-05:00", "rating": 32, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I actually found this refreshing. One of the lamest things about these fights is how the bosses say exactly the same stuff from 100% to 0% health. Kind of stupid imo.", "creationdate": "2013-06-23T21:29:57-05:00", "id": 671788, "rating": 3, "commentid": 1852569, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "alpanhell", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "It's because he is a king and he feels that he is above us. So for 25 10 to 25 ppl to kick his ass like the army of pandaren kicked his army's long ago, he's just acting like a spoiled child thinking he's entitled to the world.", "creationdate": "2013-09-27T09:57:41-05:00", "id": 696816, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1852569, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "redfinale", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Thunder King: PLAYERS OP NURF PLS!!!!!!", "creationdate": "2013-10-18T12:38:17-05:00", "id": 702087, "rating": 7, "commentid": 1852569, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Lordplatypus", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2013-05-12T19:04:30-05:00", 1, "zharshoul"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 16, "id": 1852802, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "1119903", "body": "Lol, strategy guides. Have the tank taunt and jump off platform. Lei Zhen will follow. Use loot-a-rang.", "date": "2013-05-13T18:33:02-05:00", "rating": -7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 17, "id": 1854030, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "blupache", "body": "For some reason Lei Shen currently has [url=http://www.wowpedia.org/Diminishing_returns]Diminishing Returns[/url] on Taunt turned [u]On[/u].\r\n\r\nThe Electrical Shock from Overwhelming Power is applied at a rate of about 1 per second.\r\n\r\nThis means that in the final phase tanks need to either swap at 18 stacks, or they'll run the risk of Lei Shen becoming Immune to taunts.\r\n\r\nIt's doable with either approach, but it can cause confusion where a tank is spamming taunt trying to get the boss & just ends up extending Lei Shen's taunt immunity until the tank he's is killed.", "date": "2013-05-18T09:23:30-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Taunt Diminishing Returns turned On on nearly all bosses. So many PUG/LFR tanks like to spam taunt for no reason when already tanking and when time comes to swap - bah - Immune. You can actually search logs for it, you can find Taunt Immunes on every boss. But Diminishing Returns do not \"extend infinitely\" at all. Diminishing Return timer launches when last taunt that is not immune hits, and it cannot prolong anymore. Other words, Taunts that hit Immune do not prolong the DR. So tanks can hit Immune 1 or 2 times when they're tauning too fast, but definitely not until death of the current tank.", "creationdate": "2013-05-24T09:39:42-05:00", "id": 661679, "rating": 4, "commentid": 1854030, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Varicom", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Correct, the immune is not indefinite & I wasn't clear about that. It lasts for 18 seconds after the last non-immune taunt. In LFR that may not be a death, in normal or heroic mode 18 more stacks could well be.", "creationdate": "2013-06-03T01:37:43-05:00", "id": 665567, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1854030, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "blupache", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "You can clear stacks of the phase3 tank DoT by running out during a cast, and kiting so he doesn't melee you and refresh it until it drops. Very useful on LFR when the other tank is incompetent, as you can keep your stacks down to about 24 if you kite to clear every cast of thunderstruck or lightning whip. Or be a DK and AMS instead of kiting after the boss pauses to cast.", "creationdate": "2013-07-28T04:00:56-05:00", "id": 680967, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1854030, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Karsteck", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 18, "id": 1857685, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "MasterRaistlin", "body": "Found this elsewhere, but for us it was a critical piece of info that I don't see here yet:\r\n\r\nThe base damage of [spell=135695] is 1,000,000 in 25 man (400K in 10). For each % of charge the pillar gets, the damage increases by another 10k (4K in 10). At 100% charge, the pillar would gain 1,000,000 of damage.\r\n\r\nThe pillar always gains one level (+100%) energy during the transition. Most people, depending on the order in which they take the boss to the pillars, will have between 50-90% charge on the pillar. The pillar is fully discharged at the end of the transition (hence why each pillar starts at 0% in the second phase).\r\n\r\nThus, during the transition, assuming 80 energy on the static shock pillar:\r\n\r\n1,000,000 * (1 + level) + 10k * energy = 1,000,000 * 2 + 10k * 80 = 2.8m\r\n\r\nTo become more easily survivable, you need roughly 50 or less energy on that pillar then.", "date": "2013-05-25T10:39:54-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 19, "id": 1860326, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "1124068", "body": "[u]A few tips for 25 man:[/u]\n\nEvery class can solo soak except Shamans, Holy/Disc Priests, Warriors, and DKs.\n\nDruids can use Symb on a mage for IB (Resto), CoS (Balance) or a priest for Dispersion (Feral).\n\nUse your second potion after you kill the first set of ball lightning. This will make P2 a lot smoother and let you save BL for P3.\n\nWhen you split your groups try to spread out the people who can't soak so one group doesn't have to stack all the time.\n\nYou can do a bit of \"pillar dancing\". What this means is if you're running out of pillars to charge you can move the boss in and out of the pillar. This will make it gain energy much slower at the cost of a tad extra raid damage.\n\nAnd also, don't push boss to 30% while Ball Lightning is up/going to be cast.\n\n[b]Good luck![/b]", "date": "2013-05-30T20:16:25-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2013-05-30T20:18:29-05:00", 2, "1124068"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 20, "id": 1860513, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Rogueflax", "body": "As alliance\n\nHere is a video of how we got our first kill http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Q6cXL2ZXZ7c . Difficulty is 25 man normal. Guild is soulrider of the felwen http://www.soulriders.eu/phpBB3/ on server EU-Shadowsong.\n\n[url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Q6cXL2ZXZ7c][/url]", "date": "2013-05-31T05:04:52-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2013-05-31T05:22:46-05:00", 6, "Rogueflax"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 21, "id": 1862090, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "alpanhell", "body": "Right before he dies at the end of the fight he says:\r\n\r\n[b][i]I sought only to finish... The work of the Gods...[/i][/b]\r\n\r\nNo idea what that refers to.  I see no mention on here about all the lore found on Isle of Thunder relating to Mogu and Titans too.\r\n\r\nThey also talk about Lei Shen going up on a mountain before coming down with the power of Lightning.\r\n\r\nI really like stuff like this and would hope that Blizzard would explore it further and answer the questions.  But from past experience I'm not holding my breath.\r\n\r\nWhile everyone here seems to be looking for a relationship with real word Chinese history (which I'm sure there is) there is a tie-in to the whole Titan's servants things that you saw in Northrend.  Not sure if it's a well planned story and tie-in or a lack of imagination at Blizzard.", "date": "2013-06-03T01:11:50-05:00", "rating": 20, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Actually Lorewalker Cho and Wrathion during their quest mention, that the Mogu were originally Titan constructs, bent only to their will. But when they fell silent the Mogu despaired as they were afflicted with the curse of flesh. With the power of Ra-Den however, Lei Shen was able to build an empire and reverse the curse of flesh, tough it is true, that his method was rather... brutal, but efficient nonetheless.", "creationdate": "2013-06-23T20:03:16-05:00", "id": 671771, "rating": 10, "commentid": 1862090, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Nerxedion", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I think he meant that, just like the Titans, who created everything, all the races and whatnot, Lei Shen created the Saurok, like a God.", "creationdate": "2013-07-24T12:46:00-05:00", "id": 679985, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1862090, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "FinnLich", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "You know, Ingvar says \"My life for the death god!\" when he dies... but he doesn't actually serve Yogg-Saron, commonly known as \"The Death God\" (amongst many other titles).", "creationdate": "2013-09-28T02:12:25-05:00", "id": 696998, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1862090, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "radicarl", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Ingvar is refering to the Lich King. And Lei Shen was such a brutal leader to protect the work of the titans from the mantide who served an old god.", "creationdate": "2013-11-14T16:37:22-06:00", "id": 708123, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1862090, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Lokegoathunter", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 22, "id": 1863323, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "George14", "body": "If an Assassination Rogue used Vendetta on Lei Shen, would they get[item=94524]?", "date": "2013-06-06T04:09:23-05:00", "rating": 74, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "For those who don't seem to understand [spell=79140]. \"...granting you unerring vision of your target...\"", "creationdate": "2013-06-27T09:49:15-05:00", "id": 672785, "rating": 21, "commentid": 1863323, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "ceasure", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
