{"commentv2": 1, "number": 24, "id": 1870821, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "flaotinging", "body": "With all the hype Lorewalker Cho gave this lightning guy with all the poetry and all that I was disappointed to learn he doesn't drop an Anima-fueled Saurok-bedazzled Thundering Cloud Serpent or something.\r\n\r\nAlthough... future me is bittersweetly thankful for not having to farm heroic Lei Shen on my DK at level 100.", "date": "2013-06-26T07:57:23-05:00", "rating": 32, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 25, "id": 1873159, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "Lordplatypus", "body": "He claims to be the \"Slayer of Kings and Gods\". Interestingly enough, we, the player are [i]also[/i] exactly the same, Slayers of Kings (Arthas) and Gods (C'thun, Yog'Saron). It shows that Lei Shen, while a powerful being, was only a big fish in a small pool compared to the rest of azeroth.", "date": "2013-07-03T06:52:49-05:00", "rating": 33, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Neither C'thun or Yogg-Saron have been slain, because Old Gods are extremely difficult to kill. The Titans seemingly just got lucky with Y'Shaarj and it still didn't do enough.", "creationdate": "2013-12-19T02:01:49-06:00", "id": 715557, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1873159, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "meganerd18", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Then again we are not supposed to have solo'ed the Old Gods and Arthas according to lore since we did it with the Argent Crusade or the Violet Assault, while Lei Shen did solo Ra-den and other Kings.", "creationdate": "2014-02-12T05:47:25-06:00", "id": 728109, "rating": 3, "commentid": 1873159, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "sithvincent", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Lei Shen is just an enhancement shaman", "creationdate": "2017-09-30T01:27:25-05:00", "id": 1077473, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1873159, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "anubalabeloralon", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 26, "id": 1874868, "nreplies": 5, "sticky": 0, "user": "OptimalNorway", "body": "I don't find to be as recognizeable as neither [npc=36597] or [npc=22917]. Blizzard does not represent him too well in World of Warcraft, In my opinion.", "date": "2013-07-08T13:16:01-05:00", "rating": -8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "That's because he's not the last boss of this expac", "creationdate": "2013-07-17T09:36:50-05:00", "id": 678121, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1874868, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "fang620", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Neither was Illidan.", "creationdate": "2013-07-29T20:51:47-05:00", "id": 681392, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1874868, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "NadiaEF", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Illidan was intended as the final boss for Burning Crusade. But because it was taking so long to complete Wraith and they wanted to give players something to do during the (what was it? over a year or so?) gap between Black Temple and what would be the launch of Wraith, they gave us Sunwell and the dailies that came with it to give us something to tide us over until they were ready with Wraith. They did the same thing when they added Ruby Sanctum in Wraith and used it to tide us over until Cataclysm, as well as providing a nice segway/intro into what was going to happen soon in Cataclysm.", "creationdate": "2013-08-12T02:58:57-05:00", "id": 684302, "rating": -2, "commentid": 1874868, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Kogal", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "@Kogol. Please link your source that states this. The Sunwell was a major part of the TBC storyline, and it certainly wasn't intended as a \"filler raid\" like the Ruby Sanctum was. Also, Zul'Aman was released after BT but before Sunwell - so I highly doubt what you're saying is true.", "creationdate": "2013-08-23T16:41:31-05:00", "id": 686888, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1874868, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Everliving14", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "If you quested in Mists, the Thunder King was a constantly referenced and growing threat, particularly in Kun-Lai. He was extremely well built-up. Not appearing in WC3 doesn't mean they didn't represent him well.", "creationdate": "2013-09-23T20:24:52-05:00", "id": 695879, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1874868, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Bizie", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
