{"commentv2": 1, "number": 37, "id": 2308944, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Elodeon", "body": "As of 6.2.3, 10H is doable as HFC-geared healer + DPS, as long as you keep him near an active conduit, can effectively AoE the adds, and have some kind of sprint to avoid being pushed off during intermission.", "date": "2016-02-21T22:50:50-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2016-02-21T22:51:57-06:00", 2, "Elodeon"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 38, "id": 2362591, "nreplies": 6, "sticky": 0, "user": "Shoddythetroll", "body": "as of 7.0.3 Legion Prepatch, Lei Shen knocks players back by a considerable distance everytime he goes into the intermission phase. You'll most likely die if you face your back to the edges as a result.", "date": "2016-08-07T03:31:15-05:00", "rating": 62, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This happened to me and I am not able to use the Displacement Pad to get back to his platform. A simple re-log for about a minute fixed it for me.", "creationdate": "2016-09-08T13:29:28-05:00", "id": 972255, "rating": 25, "commentid": 2362591, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Brophecy", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "A simple /reloadui will also make the teleporter to Lei-Shen platform work again :)", "creationdate": "2016-10-10T18:01:31-05:00", "id": 994699, "rating": 54, "commentid": 2362591, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Zeguy", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Thanks for this. Reload works fine", "creationdate": "2016-10-16T17:35:00-05:00", "id": 997251, "rating": 7, "commentid": 2362591, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Ethna", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I've managed to do it eventually. There was a good YouTube vid which helped. Just keep running at the dais in the centre and when he casts the wind make sure you are angled running forward away from for one of the conduits. It usually stops just short but once or twice it stopped me going over.", "creationdate": "2017-04-11T07:26:31-05:00", "id": 1043878, "rating": 4, "commentid": 2362591, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "millstoneman", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "As soon as it starts ignore everything and keep running to the center, but keep on the diagonal, i.e. facing a conduit. The distance should be long enough to keep you on the platform.", "creationdate": "2017-12-24T03:18:54-06:00", "id": 1090868, "rating": 10, "commentid": 2362591, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Jayhawk", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 39, "id": 2423338, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "Zeguy", "body": "Very hard to solo on 10man Heroic mode. Maybe impossible.\r\n\r\nAs a ilvl846 Ret pally there is too much damage going on, too many adds and you gotta watch not falling off during intermissions...so bummed as I was able to solo all the raid on heroic pretty easily (only Dark Animus was a big dps race) \r\n\r\n:(", "date": "2016-10-07T04:10:24-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Soloed as 828 bdk on 25 heroic, it was wery easy, but took 7 min to me.", "creationdate": "2016-11-06T03:18:15-06:00", "id": 1005856, "rating": -1, "commentid": 2423338, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "demonik1231", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Beast Master ilvl 807. Only died once (had to log out and in again to use the Displacement Pad). Pure luck I didn't die the second try - very caotic - and no battle pet drops at all :) very sad. I find hunters often has an advantage in soloing instances.", "creationdate": "2016-12-18T09:11:47-06:00", "id": 1017313, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2423338, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Grampshunter", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Get some more gear though. First time I soloed it on 25 hc was when I had 869 and it went easy. Now I'm 888 ilvl and it is even more easy as ret pala :D", "creationdate": "2017-02-08T10:31:01-06:00", "id": 1031164, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2423338, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Marticel", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 40, "id": 2425297, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "xavierlpp", "body": "Soloed with a BM Hunter 856 on 10H\r\nJust stay all the time in the center a do a lot of aoe to adds\r\nKill him in first try\r\n(Try to put your back to a corner, more space to walk when he push).", "date": "2016-10-09T22:37:24-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I stayed in the middle the whole time; used as much AoE (BM spec) as I could. I think the main focus (besides hitting him the whole time he's available) is to face him with your back to a corner pillar. This gives you the most space to walk (as you said) when \"Helm of Command\" is used. That helped me out a lot. 855 BM", "creationdate": "2017-02-27T23:26:58-06:00", "id": 1034939, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2425297, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "RagnCajn", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 41, "id": 2426100, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "nagi603", "body": "Solo'd on 25N with BM hunter, 110@844. It [s]can[/s] [b]will[/b] be difficult to target him, due to the sheer amount of adds, and I had to use all my active heals (artifact on kill command,exhiliration, aspect of turtle, draenei racial) and almost died on second attempt. (First attempt lasted 26 seconds, I got bumped into the chasm.) You might want to do it on 10 or bring at least a potion.", "date": "2016-10-11T07:58:43-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 42, "id": 2427049, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Hoplowe", "body": "Solo'd Heroic 10 as a BM Hunter with 844 ilvl. This fight is all about positioning and adds. \r\n\r\nZoom out the camera as far as it possibly can. Once you land in the arena, position yourself in the dead center, pick a pillar and make both your character and your camera angle face it. This pillar will be your focal point that will save you during Helm of Command. Do not move the camera angle, do not move yourself, do not face any direction other than the pillar. If you get moved by a mechanic or the angle changes with Lei Shen's movements, reclaim that spot as soon as possible. \r\n\r\nSend your pet to attack Lei Shen, but avoid doing damage yourself. You'll be out of range for Mend Pet, so duck in closer every now and then, but just focus on avoiding stuff and killing adds. The goal is to stay in the middle and reduce any damage Lei Shen can do to you before his adds show up to hurt. \r\n\r\nWhen he casts Helm of Command, which is a light blue beam that latches onto you and pushes you away, run forwards towards him - still facing the pillar you picked before. Do nothing but run forwards. You'll get close to the edge of the platform where the opposing pillar is, but because the corners with pillars are slightly longer than the other edges, you shouldn't go over it. If you get nervous, Aspect of the Cheetah negates the effect somewhat, but you won't have time to use it twice. The spell lasts eight seconds, and he used it three times against me before dying. It might take a few tries to get the hang of it, but once you do you're set for this mechanic.\r\n\r\nThe adds are more dangerous than Lei Shen once they get going. Feign Death, Misdirect, everything and anything you can do to make your pet take the brunt of it. Save your massive AOEs like Barrage and Stampede for when you start to get overwhelmed, because you will be. I popped both my (artifact boosted) Turtle as well as Exhilaration, as well as having to use the Shadow Hunter's Voodoo mask. Bring a big potion if you can. Appropriate bandages too. \r\n\r\nIt took me about four tries before I got the trick. Good luck.", "date": "2016-10-12T17:08:45-05:00", "rating": 39, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "i need to favorite this or something because my dumb ass forgets every time i go", "creationdate": "2020-07-15T00:45:09-05:00", "id": 1379304, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2427049, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "elizaday418", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 43, "id": 2439204, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Reddervish", "body": "it was suggested for hunters to use feign death to draw out the encounter. Feign death did not work (tried it twice, it did not remove agro for more than a second or two). So maybe there has been a patch to change the mechanics. I'm on a MM Hunter iLvl 848.My only AOE  is multi-shot, and its not very effective in this encounter, I do miss hunter's glaives which were taken away and given to the demon hunters with 7. will update if I get this encounter to work.", "date": "2016-11-02T16:15:09-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I just succeeded on 25 heroic as a MM hunter, ilvl 860. If you start on the bouncing bolts section of the platform, you should be able to force him to transition before you even have to move him. I chose barrage to help deal with the adds, and feign death just caused adds to return to the spots where they spawned. When I got near them, they aggroed and I had to barrage/sidewinders/marked shot to kill them. I stayed near the center of the platform to help deal with knockbacks/pushbacks. I drew aggro a couple of times, and feign got him back on my pet.", "creationdate": "2016-12-10T22:14:26-06:00", "id": 1015580, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2439204, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Urgalurg", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "My reason for Feign Death only works in conjunction with the Shadow Hunter's Voodoo Mask, which heals you for a few seconds while Feign Death is active and with this boss, right now you need all the health you can get. It's not to redirect threat, which rarely works in raids. I think it's to help mitigate bosses resetting.", "creationdate": "2016-12-26T18:02:32-06:00", "id": 1019199, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2439204, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Hoplowe", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2016-11-02T16:18:47-05:00", 1, "Reddervish"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 44, "id": 2458881, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Enina", "body": "Soloed on Heroic 25 as an 865~ Arms warrior at AP25ish. It wasn't necessarily hard, but the huge numbers of adds can clog up the screen, so if your PC sucks you might want to lower your graphics in case it could be an issue. However, you can use them to keep healing yourself.", "date": "2017-01-03T18:27:01-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 45, "id": 2476125, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Barleduq", "body": "10m Normal. BM Hunter, ilvl 815 ish, frequently fumble-fingered in trying to hit multi-shot in between everything else I'm trying to hit for this damned rotation. For my first time ever through the raid, I wasn't about to try it harder, and was mainly doing it to run it out after getting Horridon's Hide for the Legion skinning quest. My only real problem was finding Lei Shen to hit *him*, but apparently my pets didn't have a problem, cause his HP kept going down no matter what I did. Only got knocked back once; standing dead center had me with him inside the circle as he supercharged things, which made things easy. I had a harder time after getting knocked out before the second supercharge. Why*ever* would one want to prolong the encounter, is there an achievement?", "date": "2017-03-07T14:25:20-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 46, "id": 2477952, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "rrrof711", "body": "This fight was fairly easy for a Vengeance DH with about iLVL 840 average and a lvl 30 artifact weapon. Lots of jumping around. I tried to keep him and the adds on the sections of the platform that were overloaded [b][u](I guess I got lucky and had him on a different section when he started the second overload because it didn't increase the charge of the first section and I took him out after the second overload)[/u][/b]. I did quite a bit of damage to the adds but mainly focused on the boss but when there were too many after the second overload I dropped a Sigil of Flame and double Infernal Strike to wipe them all out. I must say this was the longest dungeon I have ever soloed and I only got a couple transmog but I really needed to finish this skinning Hides of Legend quest.", "date": "2017-03-17T04:31:23-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2017-03-17T04:39:08-05:00", 2, "rrrof711"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 47, "id": 2511396, "nreplies": 9, "sticky": 0, "user": "Sarthorius", "body": "For people struggling with his [spell=139011] in heroic modes (in Legion you should be doing all bosses in Heroic anyways, if you want to defeat Ra-Den next) the sprint from [item=133576] is more than enough, lots of adds spawning while the boss is untargetable, just hug the middle of the room, and keep facing the mid while killing the adds, keeping the speed buff from the food up.", "date": "2017-08-01T09:46:29-05:00", "rating": 85, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Never would have thought of that... worked like a charm.", "creationdate": "2017-08-10T12:52:39-05:00", "id": 1066593, "rating": 3, "commentid": 2511396, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "scooterjb", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This worked for me when coupled with making sure you're lined up in the longest possible route to an edge. My bear tartare didn't have a chance to work when I had dodged a crackling platform - only to shuffle me off one of the shorter edges.", "creationdate": "2017-10-03T05:43:59-05:00", "id": 1078094, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2511396, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "albinoette", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "And yeah, once he jumps to mid and star transition, I facemy back to one of the four corners, helps a bit. When you're facing away from mid to pick adds to kill (they come all to you anyway), you might move a bit off the path to a corner, just strafe back.", "creationdate": "2017-12-13T18:28:45-06:00", "id": 1089262, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2511396, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Sarthorius", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "As of today 04/19/18 This is the perfect solution for this encounter. Can I up vote you more? :)", "creationdate": "2018-04-19T15:17:43-05:00", "id": 1109202, "rating": 2, "commentid": 2511396, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "frankiecm", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "BEST. TIP. EVER.", "creationdate": "2018-04-21T20:52:19-05:00", "id": 1109453, "rating": 2, "commentid": 2511396, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Blakmane", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 48, "id": 2526530, "nreplies": 7, "sticky": 0, "user": "hoboninja", "body": "So not sure if this is a new bug or not, but if you get knocked off the platform from helm of command you cannot use the teleporter pad to get back to the fight.", "date": "2017-09-27T19:01:47-05:00", "rating": 44, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Logging in and out fixed it for me", "creationdate": "2017-09-29T17:19:16-05:00", "id": 1077424, "rating": 6, "commentid": 2526530, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Bumfuzz", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "/reload ui ....", "creationdate": "2017-10-05T14:21:58-05:00", "id": 1078429, "rating": 59, "commentid": 2526530, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "HappyAnt", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This is still the case in 8.1. /reloadui worked perfectly", "creationdate": "2019-01-07T00:59:17-06:00", "id": 1214279, "rating": 5, "commentid": 2526530, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Angelshifter", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I haven't had that issue in 8.2.", "creationdate": "2019-09-07T08:09:49-05:00", "id": 1326593, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2526530, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Vargur", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Just an FYI to those reloading that /RL is the same command", "creationdate": "2019-09-23T15:15:10-05:00", "id": 1329570, "rating": 2, "commentid": 2526530, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Neesie", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 49, "id": 2531377, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Empy3", "body": "Fairly simple to solo in 25H as a ToS geared Elemental Shaman. I did this at ilvl 928 and I do not play Elemental as a main spec, so my gear optimization is pretty bad because I go after upgrades for their Resto stats, not for Elemental. For adds, use [spell=192222], [spell=205495], and [spell=165257] on CD or when you start to see a lot of adds stacking up. Make Lei Shen your focus so you can find him in the middle of the adds. Pull with [spell=188389]], hit him with [spell=133293] and a couple of [spell=51587], reapply [spell=188389], then drop [spell=198067], hit Bloodlust [spell=71975], pop [spell=114049], and blast him with as many [spell=133293] as you can. Stay in the middle of the room and line yourself up with a diagonal so you have maximum room to work with, and use [spell=45528] and [spell=192063] during a pushback. Keep Lei Shen as your target as much as possible (this is where the focus comes in handy) and just spam [spell=50830] with him as the primary target. You can use your [spell=198103] and [spell=108271] if things start to get hairy, to buy yourself a few seconds of breathing room. It's not hard - I was expecting to take several tries before ultimately reducing the difficulty to 10H, but I killed him on 25H on the first try without ever seeing the fight before. If you have [item=137102] it will probably make this even less stressful, but I didn't have them on when I pulled and still had a relatively easy fight.", "date": "2017-10-24T14:10:20-05:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2017-10-24T14:13:03-05:00", 2, "Empy3"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 50, "id": 2543666, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "alannaliadon", "body": "In order to fight Lei Shen in Heroic mode, you must have defeated all previous bosses on Heroic.  If the raid leader switched difficulties part way through, you will need to switch back to Normal mode to see Lei Shen on the platform.", "date": "2018-01-02T14:09:41-06:00", "rating": 55, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Thank you, came for this...", "creationdate": "2018-12-13T00:37:29-06:00", "id": 1209039, "rating": 3, "commentid": 2543666, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "lobojim", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I came here looking for the solution too.. I came into instance, killed first boss and noticed that it was normal. I turned on heroic and continued. Lei Shen was not here! WTF, why are we allowed to switch and but then can't see the boss? I cannot go back and kill first boss on heroic.. So my weekly run is ruined, and Ra Den unavailable..", "creationdate": "2020-05-12T00:26:57-05:00", "id": 1368370, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2543666, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Evenuel", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I killed 2 or 3 boss in normal, then I switch to heroic mode and Lei Shen was here.", "creationdate": "2020-08-28T11:40:25-05:00", "id": 1386655, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2543666, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Overfloooooow", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 51, "id": 2559833, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Malachi68", "body": "[b]Tip for warlocks[/b]:\r\n\r\nAfter many, many tries, I figured out that [b]Demonic Circle[/b] is a fantastic way to keep Lei Shen from pushing you over the edge. When you teleport to the platform, create a circle in the middle and fight from this spot. When you start to get shoved towards the edge, use the circle to teleport back to the center. Don't wait too long because you might go out of range (and then die). Go back to the middle again and create a second circle after the cool down ticks off. Rinse and repeat as necessary (took me two times).", "date": "2018-03-26T15:44:42-05:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I took your advice and this really helped. Also make sure you are have burning rush. Between the two I was fine. Thank you.", "creationdate": "2018-12-14T18:40:46-06:00", "id": 1209540, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2559833, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Dalylah", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 52, "id": 2623274, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "giulione", "body": "Easy soloed in Heroic as a 120 prot paladin, just set your talents to have 2 charges of [url=https://www.wowhead.com/spell=190784/divine-steed]Divine Steed[/url] ([url=https://www.wowhead.com/spell=230332/cavalier]Cavalier[/url]) and you're good to go.\r\nWhen Lei Shen casts [spell=139011] just counter it with your Divine Steed, it's more than enough to outrun the push towards the edge of the platform. He will cast [spell=139011] twice during the fight, so you need the double charge just in case you burn him faster than the cooldown.", "date": "2018-10-13T15:18:42-05:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "You don't need 2 charges. I managed as RET paladin with single charge. When I got the second Helm of Command on me, CD was already reset.", "creationdate": "2018-12-22T01:51:41-06:00", "id": 1211299, "rating": 2, "commentid": 2623274, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Betonkocka", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 53, "id": 2624791, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Marco238", "body": "I just managed to completely circumvent the knockback on [spell=139011] by standing at the exact middle of the arena with Lei Shen. Not sure if i got lucky or not, will have to try to replicate!", "date": "2018-10-19T19:08:24-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Tried it and still got knocked back.", "creationdate": "2018-12-22T06:57:16-06:00", "id": 1211319, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2624791, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "lydmilla", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Read my post in this page and you'll know how to tackle the pushback, with ANY character, and cheaply.", "creationdate": "2020-04-10T22:40:58-05:00", "id": 1362290, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2624791, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Sarthorius", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2018-10-19T19:08:54-05:00", 1, "Marco238"]}
